En un mercado saturado de juegos en primera persona, aparece Homefront, una guerra cruel llena de dramatismo y oscuridad que te hará defender tu propia casa.

La historia raya en los clichés bélicos tan comunes en el género, Corea del Norte ha convertido la unión americana en un infierno, controlamos a un piloto que es hecho prisionero por las fuerzas norcoreanas, somos parte de la resistencia que busca la libertad del estado americano. La travesía nos lleva por diversos escenarios, desde escondernos del ejército enemigo en una zanja llena de cuerpos putrefactos, hasta librar una batalla encarnizada en el Golden Gate de San Francisco.

fI2Ah0A8Vxg.title: ¥T B.B. King  receiving the  Presidential Medal of Freedom ¥T
fI2Ah0A8Vxg.description:
¥T
http://www.worldblues.com/bbking/prairie/begin.html

The Presidential Medal of Freedom is the United State's highest civil award. Established by Executive Order 11085 in 1963, the Medal may be awarded by the President "to any person who has made an especially meritorious contribution to (1) the security or national interests of the United States, or (2) world peace, or (3) cultural or other significant public or private endeavors."

 An Excerpt from the President's remarks:
"One of America's unique gifts to the world is a music called the blues. And in that music two names are paramount -- B.B. King, and his guitar, Lucille. It has been said that when John Lennon was asked to name his great ambition, he said, "to play the guitar like B.B. King." Many musicians have had that same goal, but nobody has ever been able to match the skill, or copy the sound of The King of the Blues.

He came up the hard way in the Deep South; living alone when he was nine years old; walking miles to school, and picking cotton for 35 cents a day. Barely out of his teens, he made his first trip to Memphis, Tennessee, with his guitar and $2.50 in his pocket. He made his name on Beale Street, and his studio recordings made him a national favorite. B.B. King has sold more than 40 million records. He won 14 Grammys. He has a place on the Hollywood Walk of Fame. He's influenced generations of musicians from blues to rock, and he's performed in venues from roadside nightclubs to Carnegie Hall. He's still touring, and he's still recording, and he's still singing, and he's still playing the blues better than anybody else. In other words: The thrill is not gone. 

America loves the music of B.B. King, and America loves the man, himself. Congratulations. "
16 December 2006

DrArtkJF8jU.title: Mugen- Daisy vs. Petey Piranha
DrArtkJF8jU.description:
No intro or outro this time. =P 

I play as a Mugen character that is not in my team- Daisy, from Super Mario Land and other Mario game series! Daisy is an MvC + SSBB-styled character, and has strikers and attacks based on the game she first appeared on: Super Mario Land for the Game Boy. She goes up against Petey Piranha from Super Mario Sunshine, and one of the bosses from SSBB. Petey has no AI, but his supers can deal quite a lot of damage, so avoid them at all costs. He's easy to fight against, but his misaligned hitboxes and collisions can get in the way of the battle. 

Petey's HP has been raised to 3000 to make the battle longer and harder. 

BG: New York City 
BGM: Pokemon :Gold/Silver/Crystal- Lucky Number One Show/ Game Corner (remix by PokeRemixStudio) 

And in case people didn't know, Daisy has three different taunts, where she says one of the following: 
"Hi, I'm Daisy!" 
"Hey, come on!" 
"You know I'll win!"

mle8GgOmJ7U.title: Red Wolves Romp in the Snow
mle8GgOmJ7U.description:
Two of the  snow-loving captive critically endangered red wolves at the Wolf Conservation Center in South Salem, NY have some fun with our camera in between snow baths. As a participant in the Species Survival Plan under the Endangered Species Act, the WCC houses 5 critically endangered red wolves and 13 Critically endangered Mexican gray wolves. There are only about 50 Mexican gray wolves and 130 red wolves living in the wild.

To learn more about the WCC's participation in Species Survival Plans to save critically endangered wild wolves, please visit the WCC website/blog at www.nywolf.org, and follow us on Facebook at https://www.facebook.com/nywolforg and twitter at https://twitter.com/nywolforg
